article.headline: West Virginia 57, Texas 53
article.story: AUSTIN, Texas -- Aaric Murray scored 12 points and West Virginia defeated Texas 57-53 in overtime on Wednesday night. Jabarie Hinds added 11 points for the Mountaineers (8-6, 1-1 Big 12), who won their first conference game since moving over from the Big East this season. Jonathan Holmes had 12 points for Texas (8-7, 0-2), which gave up a double-digit lead in the final 5 minutes of regulation, then scored only three points in the extra period.
